quran[14]{c,v,t,f}:
  19,97,"So We have made this (the Qur’ân) easy in your own tongue (O Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم), only that you may give glad tidings to the Muttaqûn (the pious - See V.2:2), and warn with it the Ludd{1} (most quarrelsome) people.",footnotes:1:(V.97) Ludd:- The people who don’t believe in Allâh’s Oneness and His Prophet’s message and argue about everything that Allâh has ordained.
  19,98,"And how many a generation before them have We destroyed! Can you (O Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم) find a single one of them or hear even a whisper of them?"
  20,79,"And Fir‘aun (Pharaoh) led his people astray, and he did not guide them."
  20,80,"O Children of Israel! We delivered you from your enemy, and We made a covenant with you on the right side of the Mount, and We sent down to you Al-Manna {1} and quails,",footnotes:1:(V.80) See the footnote of (Verse 2:57).
  20,81,"(Saying) eat of the Tayyibât (good lawful things) wherewith We have provided you, and commit no transgression or oppression therein, lest My Anger should justly descend on you. And he on whom My Anger descends, he is indeed perished. [Tafsir At-Tabari]"
  21,55,"They said: "
  21,56,"He said: "
  21,57,""
  22,31,"Hunafâ’ Lillâh (i.e. worshiping none but Allâh), not associating partners (in worship) unto Him; and whoever assigns partners to Allâh, it is as if he had fallen from the sky, and the birds had snatched him, or the wind had thrown him to a far off place."
  22,32,"Thus it is [what has been mentioned in the above said Verses (27, 28, 29, 30, 31) is an obligation that mankind owes to Allâh] and whosoever honours the Symbols of Allâh, then it is truly from the piety of the hearts."
  22,33,"In them (cattle offered for sacrifice) are benefits for you for an appointed term, and afterwards they are brought for sacrifice unto the ancient House (the Haram - sacred territory of Makkah)."
  23,7,"But whoever seeks beyond that, then those are the transgressors;"
  23,8,"Those who are faithfully true to their Amanât (all the duties which Allâh has ordained, honesty, moral responsibility and trusts) and to their covenants;"
  23,9,"And those who strictly guard their (five compulsory congregational) Salawât (prayers) (at their fixed stated hours)."